<DOC><DOCNO> AP880503-0060 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-88 0617EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     05-03 0427</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0442</SECOND><HEAD>Tornadoes Funnel Through Kansas; Blizzard Belts Colorado</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   A severe storm droppped heavy snow on Colorado today afterwhipping up several tornadoes in Kansas.   More than a foot of snow fell on eastern Colorado, closing allroads in and out of Limon.   Strong winds brought blizzard conditions to eastern Colorado onMonday night. Up to 12 inches fell in Strasburg and 6 inches inLimon.   In central Kansas, a tornado damaged a trailer at Cheney andanother briefly touched down in open country near Lyons on Mondaynight. Several twisters were spotted around Lake Cheney and LakeAfton.   Showers and thunderstorms persisted over the area today. Showersalso prevailed from northern Louisiana and eastern Texas throughwestern Missouri, the Dakotas and the central High Plains.   Cloudy skies and light rain continued in the Northeast, whilethe Pacific Northwest received scattered showers.   Fair skies extended from the Southeast to the Great Lakes regionand in the Southwest.   Today's forecast called for rain from the northern Pacific Coastacross the Idaho Panhandle and northwest Montana; rain andoccasional thunderstorms from Arkansas across northeast Oklahoma,Missouri, Kansas, Nebraska, southeastern South Dakota and westernIowa.   Temperatures were expected to reach the upper 40s over westernNebraska; the 50s over New England, New York, the western half ofthe Dakotas, the rest of western Nebraska, much of Colorado, andthe northern half of the Pacific coast; the 80s over Florida, thecentral Gulf Coast states, Louisiana, southern Texas and southernNew Mexico; the 80s and 90s through the desert Southwest andgenerally the 60s and 70s over the rest of the nation.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 18degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 76 degrees at KeyWest, Fla.   Other reports:   _East: Atlanta 58 fair; Boston 41 rain; Buffalo 39 fair;Charleston, S.C. 53 fair; Cincinnati 54 fair; Cleveland 49 partlycloudy; Detroit 47 fair; Miami 73 fair; New York 46 cloudy;Philadelphia 45 fair; Pittsburgh 48 fair; Portland, Maine 41cloudy; Washington 49 cloudy.   _Central: Bismarck 40 rain; Chicago 53 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth64 foggy; Denver 34 fair; Des Moines 62 partly cloudy; Indianapolis52 fair; Kansas City 57 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 60 fair;Nashville 55 fair; New Orleans 62 fair; St. Louis 63 fair.   _West: Albuquerque 51 fair; Anchorage 45 cloudy; Las Vegas 56fair; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 66 fair; Salt Lake City 38 fair;San Diego 62 fair; San Francisco 52 cloudy; Seattle 42 fair.   _Canada: Montreal 37 fair; Toronto 39 partly cloudy.</TEXT></DOC>